President Obama expresses his gratitude to Commissioner Charles "Chuck" Ramsey for his nearly five decades of leadership and service in law enforcement. He commends Ramsey for his support of police officers and the communities they serve, highlighting his role as co-chair of the Task Force on 21st Century Policing. The President credits Ramsey for his contributions in bringing together leaders to create a report with key recommendations for building trust between communities and law enforcement agencies. President Obama expresses his appreciation for Ramsey's service and wishes him a peaceful retirement.